editorialSummary.text: Two-level, DJ'ed club featuring plush interiors, a garden & a year-round roof deck with river views.

originalText.text: Went for brunch. Food was completely inedible and tiny portions. The “complimentary” mimosas were left untouched they were so bad. We were given Styrofoam cups to drink from! Bar drinks are overpriced $26 for a tiny cup and also awful. The seats were grungy and ripped up. The place was completely empty besides one other small group. DJ refused song suggestions. Would not recommend

originalText.text: Awful place. We put a deposit to hold our table and they did not use it towards our bill . They put in their own gratuity. Security was super weird . The food wasn’t great . They ask to hold your license and card until you’re done eating which is very suspicious. The music felt like we were in a high school dance party .The marketing and what they promote does not match . It’s all false . Don’t waste your time or money on this place . When we were leaving- security goes “did you have a good time” I gave them a flat out honest answer - NOOOOOOO !

originalText.text: overall I’d give my experience here a 3. we came for the Halloween day party that was intended to be hosted by Dave east, but he ended up coming at 9:30 when the party started around 3:30. my friend and I ended up leaving before he came. it seemed like it was just a grab to get more publicity for the event. the drinks were extremely expensive (21 for a small cup) but we were fortunate enough that a sweet female bartender gave us 2 drinks for free. some of the staff were a little dodgy and rude as well. however the music and atmosphere was super fun, im just not sure I’d come back

originalText.text: If I can give this place 0 stars, I would definitely do so. Worst brunch experience ever. I paid 50 bucks to reserve a table from 2 to 4. Then 50 per person. The place was not ready. The DJ nor staff wasnt there. Chairs were dirty, old and broken. The rum punch and mimosas tasted so acidic and cheap. The food looked like it came from a microwave box. At 4pm they told us our reservation was up and we needed to go. We were not finished with drinks nor food. They clean our table and took our food and drinks. I never experienced that. Usually u can go and sit at the bar but the place was empty and no one was on line to wait. Bad customer service, bad food, drinks, service don't waste your time nor money...

originalText.text: This was the worst club in all of NYC. We had a table reserved and were waiting but were denied bottle service since the girls in our group were “NOT HOT ENOUGH” I have never witnessed such discrimination. This club deserves to be shut down. We paid for out table and yet did not receive the service we paid for.
